speaking of XRootD&#58; does this latest release include full EL7 support
for xrootd services -- meaning, that every restart will check for the
existence of/var/run/xrootd/, and re-create it if necessary?

The issue is that/var/run/  is on tmpfs in EL7, and gets wiped out
on reboot, so after every reboot, I have to fix this by hand,
which is less than ideal.

I haven&#39;t looked at osg-3.4, but this is a problem with all versions
I have come across on osg-3.3, including the latest 4.7.1.

So if this hasn&#39;t been fixed and there&#39;s a plan to back-port it
to osg-3.3, then I would like to request a ticket to address this.

I&#39;ve asked about this in the past, and if I remember correctly,
during the last discussion it wasn&#39;t clear whether this should
be addressed by OSG or by the xrootd developers -- but it has
to be fixed by SOMEONE.&#58;)

Also, /etc/logrotate.d/xrootd needs to be removed from the RPMs,
since xrootd does its own log rotation, so with this one being there
as well, things get double-rotated, which isn&#39;t good, either.

